Package: CausalMixGPD
Type: Package
Title: Dirichlet Process Mixtures with Generalized Pareto Tail
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Arnab Aich [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Arnab Aich <aaich@fsu.edu>
Authors@R: person("Arnab", "Aich", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "aaich@fsu.edu")
Description: Experimental framework for Dirichlet process mixture regression and unconditional models
    with flexible kernels (gamma, lognormal, normal, Laplace, inverse Gaussian, Amoroso)
    and optional generalized Pareto (GPD) tail extension. Implements Dirichlet process
    mixture models with optional GPD tail splicing for unconditional, conditional, and
    causal analyses. Inference uses stick-breaking/CRP representations and NIMBLE-backed
    MCMC. Methodological foundations include Ferguson (1973) ,
    Ishwaran and James (2001), and peaks-over-threshold
    tail theory from Balkema and de Haan (1974) and
    Pickands (1975).
